author: AccessWDUN Staff
title: White County storms to first win of season over Madison County
text:
By AccessWDUN Staff Related Articles 2015 High school football rankings 2015 High School Football region standings WEEK 6: Playoff, region races shaping up after big night VIDEO: Gainesville makes most of six Salem turnovers to set up Lanier showdown 
DANIELSVILLE — White County trailed 11-0 in the second quarter -- until Nasser Clark kicked the offense into gear. By the time the Warriors stopped they were owners of a 26-11 win over Madison County, their first victory of the 2015 season. 
Clark took a shovel pass 67 yards -- on third and 25 -- to get White County onto the scoreboard at 11-6 (the Warriors missed the 2-point conversion attempt). Clark finished the game with two touchdowns -- his second, a two yard run, giving White County a 19-11 lead. 
Thanks to the Warriors' defense, it would have been more than enough. White County (1-4, 1-1 Region 8-AAAA) held Madison County to 41 total yards in the second half and held the ball for 20 minutes, compared with just four minutes to the Red Raiders. 
Kaleb Crain paced White County with 134 yards rushing. Adam Johnson also had 40 yards rushing and a touchdown. 
The Warriors will look to keeo rolling next week against Stephens County in Cleveland. Associated Categories : Sports , High School Sports , Friday Game Night Associated Tags : High school football, White County football © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
